# Testing Guidelines

## Testing Framework

- Use Jest and React Native Testing Library for unit tests
- Use Detox for integration tests
- Follow Expo's testing tools for different environments
- Consider snapshot testing for UI consistency

## Test File Organization

- Test files mirror the component structure
- Use `__tests__/` directory for all test files
- Include mocks in `__tests__/mocks/` directory
- Follow naming convention: `ComponentName.test.tsx`

## Test Structure

- Use descriptive test names that explain the behavior
- Group related tests using `describe` blocks
- Use `beforeEach` and `afterEach` for setup and cleanup
- Mock external dependencies appropriately

## Component Testing

- Test component rendering with different props
- Test user interactions (button clicks, form submissions)
- Test conditional rendering based on props/state
- Test accessibility features and ARIA roles

## API Testing

- Mock API calls using Jest mocks
- Test both success and error scenarios
- Test loading states and error handling
- Verify correct API endpoints are called

## State Management Testing

- Test state updates and actions
- Test context providers and consumers
- Test reducer functions with different actions
- Test async state updates

## Integration Testing

- Test complete user flows
- Test navigation between screens
- Test form submissions end-to-end
- Test error scenarios and recovery

## Mock Guidelines

- Create reusable mocks in `__tests__/mocks/`
- Mock external libraries and APIs
- Use realistic mock data
- Keep mocks simple and focused

## Test Coverage

- Aim for high test coverage on critical paths
- Focus on testing business logic
- Don't test implementation details
- Test edge cases and error conditions

## Performance Testing

- Test component rendering performance
- Test memory leaks in long-running tests
- Use React Native Testing Library's performance utilities
- Monitor test execution time
